  "nursesNote": "Discharge planning for a psychiatric patient begins at admission to ensure a smooth, safe transition. The nurse confirms a clear medication plan and how the patient will obtain medications, sets up outpatient follow-up appointments, and connects the patient to community resources such as case management (or an assertive community treatment team for severe illness), support and peer groups, and step-down levels of care like partial hospitalization (PHP) or intensive outpatient (IOP). Basic needs (housing, food, finances, transportation) are addressed. The nurse provides a crisis plan with a hotline number and who to call, teaches warning signs of relapse, and gives written instructions while confirming understanding with teach-back. Family education and a safety net help prevent readmission.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Begin discharge planning at admission",
    "Confirm the medication plan and access",
    "Arrange outpatient follow-up and appropriate level of care",
    "Connect to community resources and support",
    "Provide a crisis plan and confirm understanding"
  ],
